    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A type of kantharos featuring handles and bowl much as in type B, a small torus foot with no stem, and a bowl usually decorated with patterns rather than figures. The name comes from the botanical term 'sessile' denoting something sitting directly on its base.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046899/Clark, Elston and Hart, Understanding Greek Vases (2002)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een type kantharoi met handvatten en een kom grotendeels zoals in type B, alsmede een kleine torusvoet zonder steel, waarvan de kom meestal is versierd met patronen in plaats van figuren. De naam komt van de botanische term 'sessiel' die ‘ongesteeld, direct op de basis’ betekent.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種康塔羅斯酒杯，握把及杯身特徵與B型相似，具有小的圓凸線腳杯座，不具杯柄，杯身通常以花樣圖案為裝飾而非人像。名稱來自植物學的詞彙「無柄」，代表某物直接座落於基底。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
